    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I agree this behavior is surprising. Unfortunately, this is how Python defines `~` for booleans:\n\n```\nIn [20]: ~False\nOut[20]: -1\n\nIn [21]: ~True\nOut[21]: -2\n```\n\nWe could do more aggressive dtype inference to cast the first array to `dtype=bool`, but would likely have severe negative performance implications.\n"
  },
